   "source": [
    "# Tutorial 1: Regressors from ecg"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ddbfb1b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This example shows how to use *niphlem* for one subject from one of our particular projects. These data consist of one acquisition of resting-state that has been previously preprocesses using *fMRIPrep* and physiological acquired through a Siemens multiband protocol. For the sake of simplicity in this example, we are going to concentrate only on cardiac signal reprsented by the ECG. \n",
    "\n",
    "In addition, we are going to show the maps generated by the *niphlem* generated regressors using the library *nilearn* (https://nilearn.github.io/)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "50d57fb5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/home/javi/.local/lib/python3.8/site-packages/nilearn/datasets/__init__.py:86: FutureWarning: Fetchers from the nilearn.datasets module will be updated in version 0.9 to return python strings instead of bytes and Pandas dataframes instead of Numpy arrays.\n",
      "  warn(\"Fetchers from the nilearn.datasets module will be \"\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# IMPORTS\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "from nilearn import image, plotting\n",
    "from nilearn.glm.first_level import FirstLevelModel\n",
    "\n",
    "from niphlem.input_data import (load_cmrr_info, load_cmrr_data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3aac89fc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's start definining our data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "7c8ae3c6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Our preprocessed BOLD image\n",
    "run_img = image.load_img(\"data/demo/sub-06_ses-04_task-resting_run-01_space-MNI152NLin2009cAsym_desc-preproc_bold.nii.gz\")\n",
    "# The repetition time of the scanner\n",
    "t_r = 1.5\n",
    "# The frame times, used to define the regressors at the precise times\n",
    "n_vols = run_img.shape[-1]\n",
    "frame_times = np.arange(n_vols)*t_r\n",
    "# Our file with the confounder regressors as a Dataframe. It will be used later to extract the motion parameters\n",
    "conf_df = pd.read_csv(\"data/demo/sub-06_ses-04_task-resting_run-01_desc-confounds_regressors.tsv\", sep=\"\\t\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Our physiological data, the info log file and the ECG log file\n",
    "info_log = \"./data/demo/physio/Physio_20210322_140315_89a222d1-4c24-4caf-a898-f06c6bfd2342_Info.log\"\n",
    "ecg_log = \"./data/demo/physio/Physio_20210322_140315_89a222d1-4c24-4caf-a898-f06c6bfd2342_ECG.log\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d6c43c5e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Load data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "59453716",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The first thing that we need is to load the info file, which will give us the times of the scanner. We can load this kind of the data using the function `niphlem.input_data.load_cmrr_info`. The only thing that we have to do is to pass the info log file to this function, and it will return the time traces and a dictionary with some meta information which is at the beginning of the file."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "d768a82d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "time_traces, meta_info = load_cmrr_info(info_log)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "a8bd913e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'uuid': '89a222d1-4c24-4caf-a898-f06c6bfd2342',\n",
       " 'scan_date': '20210322_140315',\n",
       " 'log_version': 'EJA_1',\n",
       " 'n_slices': 68,\n",
       " 'n_vols': 353,\n",
       " 'n_echoes': 1,\n",
       " 'init_physio': 20241969,\n",
       " 'end_physio': 20457989,\n",
       " 'init_scan': 20246200,\n",
       " 'end_scan': 20457978,\n",
       " 'repetition_time': 600.0}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "meta_info"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9060e82f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now that we have the time traces, we are going to load our ECG data by passing to the function `niphlem.input_data.load_cmrr_data` its log file and the meta information dictionary that we've just generated. This dictionary is required to be able to synchronize the physiological signal with the scanner times. We also specify the type of signal, as a new entry to an updated dictionary will be added, containing meta information of this ECG signal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "5f96bb49",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ecg_signal, meta_info = load_cmrr_data(ecg_log, info_dict=meta_info, sig_type=\"cardiac\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "be54fb41",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's have a look into a portion of this signal, corresponding to 2 s"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "8f739efd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

    "plt.plot(1000 + ecg_signal[:,1], label=\"electrode 2\")\n",
    "plt.plot(2000 + ecg_signal[:,2], label=\"electrode 3\")\n",
    "plt.plot(3000 + ecg_signal[:,3], label=\"electrode 4\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",

    "pass"
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},

    "Let's also have a look at the updated information dictionary."
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fcac846b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Retroicor regressors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1c0d8bc6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's start the generation of regressors for the Retroicor Model. The class for generating these regressors is found as `niphlem.models.RetroicorPhysio`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "8a206f05",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from niphlem.models import RetroicorPhysio"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "47ac84c6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's have a look at the documentation of the class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "0e4affd6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "     Physiological regressors using Retroicor.\n",
      "\n",
      "    Parameters\n",
      "    ----------\n",
      "    physio_rate : float\n",
      "        Sampling rate for the recording in Hz.\n",
      "        This is needed for filtering to define the nyquist frequency.\n",
      "    t_r : float\n",
      "        Repetition time for the scanner (the usual T_R) in secs.\n",
      "    delta: float\n",
      "        minimum separation (in physio recording units) between\n",
      "        events in signal to be considered peaks\n",
      "    peak_rise: float\n",
      "        relative height with respect to the 20th tallest events in signal\n",
      "        to consider events as peak.\n",
      "    order: int or array-like (# TODO) of shape (n_orders,)\n",
      "        Fourier expansion for phases. If int, the fourier expansion is\n",
      "        performed to that order, starting from 1. If an array is provided,\n",
      "        each element will multiply the phases.\n",
      "    transform : {\"mean\", \"zscore\", \"abs\"}, optional\n",
      "        Transform data before filtering. The default is \"mean\".\n",
      "    filtering : {\"butter\", \"gaussian\", None}, optional\n",
      "        Filtering operation to perform. The default is None.\n",
      "    high_pass : float, optional\n",
      "        High-pass filtering frequency (in Hz). Only if filtering option\n",
      "        is not None. The default is None.\n",
      "    low_pass : float, optional\n",
      "        Low-pass filtering frequency (in Hz). Only if filtering option\n",
      "        is not None. The default is None.\n",
      "    columns : List or array of n_channels elements, \"mean\" or None, optional\n",
      "        It describes how to handle input signal channels. If a list, it will\n",
      "        weight each channel and take the dot product. If \"mean\",\n",
      "        the average across the channels. If None, it will consider each\n",
      "        channel separately. The default is None.\n",
      "    n_jobs : int, optional\n",
      "        Number of jobs to consider in parallel. The default is 1.\n",
      "    \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(RetroicorPhysio.__doc__)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "328ceb46",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We have three required arguments (physio_rate, t_r, delta) and a bunch of optional ones. In our case *physio_rate* is 400 Hz, t_r is 1.5 s and delta=200, the minimu separation between peaks and that corresponds to 200, i.e. 2 peaks per second or at most 120 peaks per minute. \n",
    "\n",
    "Before the computing any regressors, we are going to take the mean signal across all the for electrodes and then filter the signal between 0.5 and 3.0 Hz.\n",
    "\n",
    "Finally, retroicor regressors of order 2 will be generated."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "2f4a6e7b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "retro_ecg = RetroicorPhysio(physio_rate=400, # Physiological rate (400 Hz)\n",
    "                            t_r=1.5, # Scan rate (1.5 s)\n",
    "                            delta=200, \n",
    "                            columns=\"mean\", # mean across the four electrodes\n",
    "                            filtering=\"butter\", # a butterworth filter\n",
    "                            low_pass=3.0, # keep frequencies below this\n",
    "                            high_pass=0.5, # keep frequencies above this\n",
    "                            order=2 # order 2 of the retroicor expansion\n",
    "                           )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e9ad81d3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Once we have defined this object, we generate the regressors using the method `compute_regressors`, which is comon to all the models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "59ff5a32",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "retroicor_regressors = retro_ecg.compute_regressors(signal=ecg_signal, time_scan=frame_times)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ef47fa13",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's see the a part of these regressors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "5280b9d3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 504x360 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7,5))\n",
    "plt.plot(frame_times, retroicor_regressors[:,0], label=\"sin1\")\n",
    "plt.plot(frame_times, 3 + retroicor_regressors[:,1], label=\"cos1\")\n",
    "plt.plot(frame_times, 6 + retroicor_regressors[:,2], label=\"sin2\")\n",
    "plt.plot(frame_times, 9 + retroicor_regressors[:,3], label=\"cos2\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"time (s)\")\n",
    "plt.xlim([0,100])\n",
    "pass"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bb0dd737",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
    "dm_retroicor = np.column_stack((np.ones(len(frame_times)), # Intercept\n",
    "                                conf_df.filter(regex=\"rot|trans\").to_numpy(), # Motion parameters\n",
    "                                retroicor_regressors # ECG regressors\n",
    "                               ))\n",
    "dm_retroicor = pd.DataFrame(dm_retroicor, \n",
    "                            columns=[\"intercept\", \n",
    "                                     \"trans_x\",\"trans_y\",\"trans_z\",\"rot_x\",\"rot_y\",\"rot_z\",\n",
    "                                     \"sin1\", \"cos1\", \"sin2\", \"cos2\"\n",
    "                                      ]\n",
    "                     )\n",
    "dm_retroicor.index=frame_times\n",
    "dm_retroicor.head()"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "4f234347",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.pcolormesh(dm_retroicor)\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(0.5 + np.arange(dm_retroicor.shape[1]))\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2e7285af",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now fit this design matrix to our BOLD image"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "57a80b93",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "first_level = FirstLevelModel(t_r=t_r, drift_model=None, signal_scaling=False, smoothing_fwhm=6)\n",
    "first_level.fit(run_imgs=run_img, design_matrices=dm_retroicor)\n",
    "retroicor_map = first_level.compute_contrast(\"sin1+cos1+sin2+cos2\", stat_type=\"F\", output_type=\"z_score\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "8e713c43",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<nilearn.plotting.displays.OrthoProjector at 0x7f55a05d9250>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 16,
     "metadata": {},
